claim.claim-text:
The battery module according to claim 3, wherein
a part of the explosion-proof valve (13) of each battery (1) is covered by the first bending portion (22) of the first heat exchange plate (2) in the width direction (W);
the battery module further comprises a second heat exchange plate (3), the second heat exchange plate (3) comprising: a second main body portion (31) (31) located on the other side of the plurality of batteries (1) in the width direction (W); and a second bending portion (32) bending from an upper side of the second main body portion (31) to the plurality of batteries (1) along the width direction (W), the other part of the explosion-proof valve (13) of each battery (1) being covered by the second bending portion (32) in the width direction (W); and a flow channel for flow of a heat exchange medium is disposed in the second bending portion (32), and the second bending portion (32) is configured to be capable of leaking the heat exchange medium in the flow channel after being melted.

The battery module according to claim 1, wherein an explosion-proof valve (13) of each battery (1) is disposed at an end part of the top cover (10) in the width direction (W), and explosion-proof valves (13) of the plurality of batteries (1) are located on two sides in the width direction (W);
the battery module further comprises a second heat exchange plate (3), the second heat exchange plate (3) comprising: a second main body portion (31); and a second bending portion (32) bending from an upper side of the second main body portion (31) to the plurality of batteries (1) along the width direction (W), a flow channel for flow of a heat exchange medium being disposed in the second bending portion (32), and the second bending portion (32) being configured to be capable of leaking the heat exchange medium in the flow channel after being melted;
the first main body portion (21) and the second main body portion (31) are located on two sides of the plurality of batteries (1) in the width direction (W); and explosion-proof valves (13) on corresponding sides are covered by the first bending portion (22) and the second bending portion (32) in the width direction (W).

The battery module according to claim 1, wherein explosion-proof valves (13) of some batteries (1) are disposed at end parts of corresponding top covers (10) in the width direction (W), and explosion-proof valves (13) of the plurality of batteries (1) are located on a same side in the width direction (W); explosion-proof valves (13) of the other batteries (1) are disposed between corresponding first electrode terminals (11) and corresponding second electrode terminals (12); the explosion-proof valves (13) of the some batteries (1) are covered by the first bending portion (22) of the first heat exchange plate (2) in the width direction (W);

the battery module further comprises a second heat exchange plate (3) comprising:

a second main body portion (31) located on the other side of the plurality of batteries (1) in the width direction (W); and a second bending portion (32) bending from an upper side of the second main body portion (31) to the plurality of batteries (1) along the width direction (W), the explosion-proof valves (13) of the other batteries (1) being covered by the second bending portion (32) in the width direction (W); and a flow channel for flow of a heat exchange medium is disposed in the second bending portion (32), and the second bending portion (32) is configured to be capable of leaking the heat exchange medium in the flow channel after being melted.
